  <front>
   <head>SONNET [48] XLVIII. To Mrs. ****.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="pentameter">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">NO more my wearied soul attempts to stray</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">From sad Reality and vain Regret,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Nor courts enchanting Fiction to allay</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Sorrows that Sense refuses to forget:</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">For of Calamity so long the prey,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Imagination now has lost her pow'rs,</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Nor will her fairy loom again essay</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">To dress Affliction in a robe of flow'rs.</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">But if no more the bow'rs of Fancy bloom,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Let one superior scene attract my view,</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Where Heav'n's pure rays the sacred spot illume,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Let  lov'd hand with palm and am'ranth strew</l>
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">The mournful path approaching to the tomb,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="12">While Faith's consoling voice endears the friendly gloom.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
